(5138, '_transient_dash_8ed47f02370e4304b3fb8352267b4572', '<div class=\"rss-widget\"><ul><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://wordpress.org/news/2018/08/wordpress-4-9-8-maintenance-release/\'>WordPress 4.9.8 Maintenance Release</a> <span class=\"rss-date\">Agosto 2, 2018</span><div class=\"rssSummary\">We are pleased to announce the immediate availability of WordPress 4.9.8.  This maintenance release fixes 46 bugs, enhancements and blessed tasks, including updating the Twenty Seventeen bundled theme. Following are the highlights of what is now available. “Try Gutenberg” callout Most users will now be presented with a notice in their WordPress dashboard. This “Try Gutenberg” [&hellip;]</div></li></ul></div><div class=\"rss-widget\"><ul><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://wptavern.com/wpweekly-episode-329-gutenberg-forks-and-wordpress-development-cycles\'>WPTavern: WPWeekly Episode 329 – Gutenberg, Forks, and WordPress Development Cycles</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://wptavern.com/distributor-plugin-now-publicly-available-adds-gutenberg-support\'>WPTavern: Distributor Plugin Now Publicly Available, Adds Gutenberg Support</a></li><li><a class=\'rsswidget\' href=\'https://wptavern.com/gutenberg-contributors-considering-a-focus-mode-for-writing\'>WPTavern: Gutenberg Contributors Considering a “Focus Mode” for Writing</a></li></ul></div>', 'no');
